  "text": "Since the Kupalov's place reflex is basically an instrumental paradigm in which the signal occurs as a result of subject-experimenter interaction [CITATION_1] , it was not possible to tell whether the signal-related activities were due to a Pavlovian CS-US relationship or a learned operant response-reinforcer relationship. This problem will be elaborated upon later.",
