      "span_text": "Since the Kupalov's place reflex is basically an instrumental paradigm in which the signal occurs as a result of subject-experimenter interaction  , it was not possible to tell whether the signal-related activities were due to a Pavlovian CS-US relationship or a learned operant response-reinforcer relationship."
